Pronotum (
Figs. 1–2
) in dorsal view approximately bell-shaped, with rounded anterior margin and anterior parts of lateral margins, without anterior corners, with shallow constriction in posterior half; hind corners obtuseangled and blunt; posterior margin arcuate; lateral marginal carinae visible in posterior half or third as rather blunt edges; base of pronotum with distinct arcuate transverse groove connecting one lateral pair of shallow pits; sublateral carinae absent; pronotum only with thin setae, without thick bristles.

