Elytra (
Figs. 1–2
) oval, each with two asetose rudiments of basal foveae, of which external one is more distinct, with short basal impression; humeral calli distinct and developed as longitudinal protuberances; subhumeral lines absent.

Abdominal sternites (
Fig. 9
